[size=4][b]Support[/b][/size]

[size=3]Continued development, testing, &amp; managing user reports all take time; any support is greatly appreciated![/size]

[url=https://ko-fi.com/p1xel8ted][img]https://ko-fi.com/img/githubbutton_sm.svg[/img][/url]

[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Shows each zombie's work efficiency in a label floating over its head, readable across the whole graveyard without inspecting bodies one at a time.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Pick what to show[/b] - tick any combination of percentage, white-skull count, and the station each zombie is working at (or "Idle" when unassigned). Numbers share the top line; the job sits on the line below.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Toggle on demand[/b] - press the key (default B) or a controller button to show or hide the labels.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Colour-coded[/b] - the numbers shade from red (low) to green (high), or switch to plain white in the settings.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Place it right[/b] - adjust text size and nudge the labels up, down, left, or right.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url], press F1 in-game to open the config interface - rebind the key, set a controller button, choose which details to show, adjust size and position, or have the labels start hidden.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:[/size]

[code]...\steamapps\common\Graveyard Keeper\BepInEx[/code]

